  <div class="page" id="page-scenarios">
    <div style="padding:32px">
      <div class="section-hdr"><h2>Real-Life Scenarios</h2><div class="section-hdr-line"></div></div>
      <p style="font-size:13px; color:var(--text2); margin-bottom:24px">Situations you'll actually face as a data analyst — with how to approach them.</p>

      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div style="display:flex; gap:10px; margin-bottom:8px">
          <span style="background:rgba(245,158,11,0.1);color:var(--gold);font-size:11px;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:99px;font-weight:600">E-Commerce</span>
          <span style="background:rgba(239,68,68,0.1);color:var(--red);font-size:11px;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:99px;font-weight:600">Urgent</span>
        </div>
        <div class="scenario-title">🚨 Revenue dropped 23% last Tuesday. CEO wants answers in 2 hours.</div>
        <div class="scenario-context">Platform: Flipkart-style e-commerce. You have access to orders, sessions, product, and payment tables.</div>
        <ol class="scenario-steps" style="padding-left:4px">
          <li><strong>Isolate the change:</strong> Compare Tuesday vs same-day last week/last month. Confirm it's real, not a reporting issue (check if data pipeline ran).</li>
          <li><strong>Decompose the metric:</strong> Revenue = Sessions × Conversion × AOV. Which component dropped?</li>
          <li><strong>Segment analysis:</strong> By device (mobile/web), region, category, payment method. Where is the drop concentrated?</li>
          <li><strong>Correlate with events:</strong> Did a promo expire? App update deployed? Payment gateway outage? Look at error logs + order_status breakdown.</li>
          <li><strong>SQL to run:</strong> <code style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;color:var(--teal)">SELECT hour, COUNT(*) as orders, SUM(amount), AVG(amount) FROM orders WHERE date IN ('this_tue','last_tue') GROUP BY 1,2</code></li>
          <li><strong>Communicate:</strong> Share a 5-point Slack summary: what happened, when, where, likely cause, next steps. Don't wait for perfect analysis.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div style="display:flex; gap:10px; margin-bottom:8px">
          <span style="background:rgba(59,130,246,0.1);color:var(--blue);font-size:11px;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:99px;font-weight:600">Product Analytics</span>
        </div>
        <div class="scenario-title">📊 PM asks: "Should we keep or kill Feature X?"</div>
        <div class="scenario-context">Feature was launched 3 months ago. PM wants data to decide in next week's roadmap review.</div>
        <ol class="scenario-steps" style="padding-left:4px">
          <li><strong>Define success metrics:</strong> What was the original goal? Adoption rate, engagement, retention lift, revenue attribution?</li>
          <li><strong>Adoption funnel:</strong> % users who saw feature → tried it → used it weekly. Calculate day-1, day-7, day-30 retention for feature users vs non-users.</li>
          <li><strong>Causal question:</strong> Is retention better because users are better, or because the feature drives retention? Propensity matching or pre/post analysis.</li>
          <li><strong>Business impact:</strong> If feature improves D30 retention by 5%, what's the revenue impact at current scale?</li>
          <li><strong>Recommendation format:</strong> "Feature X has 12% adoption, users who engage with it have 8pp higher 30-day retention (statistically significant at p=0.02). Recommend keep + improve discoverability."</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div style="display:flex; gap:10px; margin-bottom:8px">
          <span style="background:rgba(20,184,166,0.1);color:var(--teal);font-size:11px;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:99px;font-weight:600">Marketing Analytics</span>
        </div>
        <div class="scenario-title">🎯 Which marketing channel has the best ROI?</div>
        <div class="scenario-context">Marketing team has campaigns running across Google Ads, Meta, influencers, email. Budget allocation decision next month.</div>
        <ol class="scenario-steps" style="padding-left:4px">
          <li><strong>Define the funnel:</strong> Attribution model — last-click? First-click? Multi-touch? Agree on this first.</li>
          <li><strong>Calculate CAC per channel:</strong> CAC = Channel Spend / New Customers acquired via that channel</li>
          <li><strong>LTV by acquisition channel:</strong> Customers from Channel X — what's their 90-day, 180-day revenue?</li>
          <li><strong>ROI = (LTV − CAC) / CAC</strong> — compare across channels. A channel with higher CAC may have 3x LTV.</li>
          <li><strong>Cohort quality:</strong> Do Google Ads customers churn faster than organic? Retention curves by channel tell the real story.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div style="display:flex; gap:10px; margin-bottom:8px">
          <span style="background:rgba(124,106,247,0.1);color:var(--accent);font-size:11px;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:99px;font-weight:600">Data Quality</span>
        </div>
        <div class="scenario-title">🔍 Your analysis shows 1M users. Finance says it should be 800K. Who is right?</div>
        <div class="scenario-context">Escalated discrepancy between your dashboard and finance's report. Leadership involved.</div>
        <ol class="scenario-steps" style="padding-left:4px">
          <li><strong>Don't defend your number immediately.</strong> First understand the discrepancy.</li>
          <li><strong>Define "user":</strong> Are you counting unique user_ids? Finance may count billing accounts. These are different.</li>
          <li><strong>Check date ranges, filters, deduplication logic.</strong> Run row counts at each transformation step.</li>
          <li><strong>Compare source tables:</strong> What table/source did each report use? Document the lineage.</li>
          <li><strong>Outcome:</strong> Create a data dictionary entry defining "active user" precisely. Agree on a single source of truth. Both numbers may be correct for different definitions.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

